Perpetual Ltd. | Asia Pacific
Unchanged Impact to our thesis
Modest shortfall Financial results versus consensus
Modest revision lower Direction of next 12-month consensus EPS
Source: Company data, Morgan Stanley Research
PPT missed MS / cons by \(1 - 2\%\) at EBITDA, though a lower tax rate saw UNPAT 1- \(3\%\) ahead. Dividend was \(2\%\) below cons.
Corporate Trust a standout growing EBITDA \(9\%\) Y/Y and is launching a digital marketplace for debt instruments, boding well for further growth.
Base fees in Investments fell 2bp Y/Y, though stronger performance fees in Pendal helped to shield revenues. EBITDA fell \(2\%\) Y/Y despite higher FUM.
Wealth EBITDA fell \(4\%\) Y/Y, missing cons / MS by \(10\%\) on lower FUM revenues, lower fees & one- off legal plus retention payments. Timing of FA moves impacted fees.
We view this as a mixed update; the asset manager has a substantial body of work ahead to improve earnings growth.
MORGAN STANLEY AUSTRALIA LIMITED+
Andrei Stadnik, FIAA
Daniel N Bounpraseuth
Perpetual Ltd. (PPT.AX, PPT AU)

- Investments valued on a P/E multiple of 9x FY26e, in line with peers in outflows.- Corporate Trust on a P/E multiple of 17x FY26e to reflect strategic appeal and quality earnings growth.- Perpetual Private on a P/E multiple of 12x FY26e, at the upper end of peers given consistent inflows.- Group & Services costs capitalised at \(\sim 12x\) FY26e EPS.
- Higher equity prices- More products and greater cross-selling- Perpetual Private winning more advisors and FUA- Improving flows
- Market volatility, affecting retail confidence and inflows- Investment revenue margin pressure accelerates- Departure of key investment or sales staff- Cost inflation, particularly wages

Not-Rated (NR). Currently the analyst does not have adequate conviction about the stock's total return relative to the average total return of the analyst's industry (or industry team's) coverage universe, on a risk-adjusted basis, over the next 12-18 months.
